						<div class="postbody">From INL...<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Mapper 5: MMC5 ExROM<br />A simplified version that supports large memories of MMC5 may be possible</div><br /><br />Sounds like...If all you need is extra ROM space, then yes.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">in-game effects</div><br /><br />what does this mean?<br /><br />3.MMC5 is the most complicated *Nintendo mapper. If all you are doing is swapping ROM banks, shouldn't be too bad.<br /><br />4.Lots of mappers would work for an RPG.<br /><br />*Konami VRC7 might be more complicated, due to unusual audio chip.<br /><br /><br />EDIT, I personally like CHR-RAM...but if you don't, maybe use MMC3, which is available from INL.</div>

					
